',NULL),(152,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Urgent: System Maintenance Scheduled\n\nDear Valued Customers,\n\nPlease be advised that we will be performing essential system maintenance this weekend. This maintenance is crucial to ------- (5) ------- the performance and security of our online services. The maintenance window is scheduled to begin on Saturday, July 20th, at 10:00 PM and will conclude by Sunday, July 21st, at 6:00 AM.\n\nDuring this period, our website and mobile application may be temporarily unavailable. We understand that this may cause some ------- (6) -------, and we sincerely apologize for it. Our technical team will work diligently to minimize the downtime and restore full service as quickly as possible.\n\n------- (7) -------. We recommend that you complete any urgent transactions before the maintenance period begins. All stored data and account information will remain secure and unaffected by this process.\n\nThank you for your understanding and ------- (8) -------.\n\nSincerely,\nThe Tech Support Team','READING','Part 6 - Passage 002 (System Maintenance Notice)',NULL),(153,NULL,NULL,6,'Headline: Enhance Your Career with Our Project Management Workshop!\n\nAre you looking to improve your project management skills and advance your career? Our intensive two-day workshop is designed for professionals who want to learn the latest methodologies and best practices in the field. ------- (9) -------.\n\nThe workshop will cover key topics such as project planning, risk management, team leadership, and budget control. Our experienced instructors are certified professionals with years of real-world experience. They will provide practical insights and hands-on exercises to help you ------- (10) ------- the concepts effectively. Each participant will receive a comprehensive set of course materials and a certificate of completion.\n\nSpace is limited, so early registration is ------- (11) ------- encouraged. Register by March 15th to receive a 10% early bird discount. You can find more details and register online at www.pmworkshops.com.\n\nDon\'t miss this ------- (12) ------- to invest in your professional development!\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 003 (Course Advertisement)',NULL),(154,NULL,NULL,6,'To: All Employees\nFrom: Office Administration\nDate: May 31, 2025\nSubject: Implementation of New Recycling Policy\n\nDear Employees,\n\nEffective next Monday, June 9th, we will be ------- (13) ------- a new and improved recycling policy throughout all office locations. This initiative is part of our ongoing commitment to environmental sustainability and reducing our corporate footprint.\n\nUnder the new policy, separate bins for paper, plastic, and general waste will be placed in all common areas, including kitchens and copy rooms. ------- (14) -------. Detailed guidelines on what can and cannot be recycled in each bin will be posted above each station and also circulated via email. We encourage everyone to familiarize ------- (15) ------- with these guidelines to ensure the program\'s success.\n\nYour participation is crucial. Proper sorting of waste materials will significantly help us achieve our recycling goals and contribute to a greener work environment. We ------- (16) ------- your full cooperation in adhering to this new policy.\n\nThank you,\nOffice Administration','READING','Part 6 - Passage 004 (Office Memo: New Recycling Policy)',NULL),(155,NULL,NULL,6,'To: Project Team Leads\nFrom: David Miller, Project Director\nSubject: Update on Project Alpha Deadline\n\nDear Team Leads,\n\nI am writing to inform you about an adjustment to the deadline for Project Alpha. Due to some unforeseen technical challenges we ------- (17) ------- last week, it has become necessary to extend the final submission date.\n\nThe new deadline for all project deliverables is now Friday, August 22nd. This extension should provide sufficient time to address the issues and ensure the quality of our final product. ------- (18) -------. We believe this additional time will allow all teams to complete their tasks thoroughly.\n\nPlease update your project timelines ------- (19) ------- and inform your respective team members of this change. It is important that we all work diligently to meet this revised deadline. Regular progress meetings will continue as scheduled.\n\nThank you for your understanding and continued ------- (20) -------.\n\nSincerely,\nDavid Miller','READING','Part 6 - Passage 005 (Email: Project Deadline Extension)',NULL),(156,NULL,NULL,6,'Headline: Get Fit, Feel Great at Peak Fitness Center!\n\nAre you ready to achieve your fitness goals? Peak Fitness Center is excited to announce its grand opening on July 1st! We offer state-of-the-art equipment, a wide ------- (21) ------- of group fitness classes, and personal training sessions with certified instructors.\n\nOur facility includes a spacious weightlifting area, modern cardio machines, a yoga studio, and luxurious locker rooms. ------- (22) -------. Whether you are a beginner or a seasoned athlete, our friendly staff is here to support you every step of the way. We are committed to providing a clean, safe, and ------- (23) ------- environment for all our members.\n\nSign up before June 30th and receive a special founding member discount, plus a free personal training consultation. Visit our website at www.peakfitness.com to learn more about our membership ------- (24) ------- and class schedules.\n\nDon\'t wait – start your fitness journey with us today!\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 006 (Fitness Center Advertisement)',NULL),(157,NULL,NULL,6,'The rise of remote work has significantly transformed the modern workplace. Many companies have adopted flexible work arrangements, allowing employees to work from home or other locations outside the traditional office. This shift ------- (25) ------- numerous benefits, such as increased autonomy and reduced commuting time for employees.\n\nHowever, remote work also presents certain challenges. Maintaining strong team cohesion and ensuring effective communication can be more difficult when team members are not physically present in the same location. ------- (26) -------. Companies are ------- (27) ------- exploring various tools and strategies to address these issues, including virtual team-building activities and enhanced digital communication platforms.\n\nThe long-term effects of widespread remote work are still being studied, but it is clear that this model is here to stay. Businesses that successfully adapt to this new ------- (28) ------- will likely have a competitive advantage in attracting and retaining talent.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 007 (Article: Remote Work Impact)',NULL),(158,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Upcoming Workshop: Mastering Digital Marketing\n\nDear Professionals,\n\nWe are pleased to announce an upcoming workshop titled \"Mastering Digital Marketing,\" scheduled for August 5-6. This intensive program is designed to ------- (29) ------- participants with the latest strategies and tools in the ever-evolving world of digital marketing.\n\nThe workshop will feature sessions led by industry experts, covering topics such as SEO, content marketing, social media strategy, and data analytics. ------- (30) -------. Attendees will have the opportunity to network with peers and gain valuable insights that can be immediately applied to their work. The primary goal is to help you create more ------- (31) ------- and measurable marketing campaigns.\n\nRegistration is now open, and space is limited. An early bird discount is available for those who register before July 15th. For more information on the agenda and to secure your spot, please visit our website. We are confident this workshop will be a valuable ------- (32) ------- for your professional growth.\n\nWe hope to see you there!\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 008 (Workshop Announcement)',NULL),(159,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Regarding Your Application for Marketing Specialist\n\nDear Mr. John Kirby,\n\nThank you for your interest in the Marketing Specialist position at Innovatech Solutions and for taking the time to interview with our team last week. We were very ------- (33) ------- with your qualifications and experience.\n\nThe hiring committee has carefully reviewed all applications and conducted interviews with a number of highly qualified candidates. ------- (34) -------. While your background is certainly strong, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose profile more closely matches the specific requirements of this particular role at this time.\n\nThis was a very difficult decision due to the high ------- (35) ------- of applicants. We will keep your resume on file for future openings that may be a better fit for your skills. We appreciate you considering Innovatech Solutions and wish you the best of luck in your job ------- (36) -------.\n\nSincerely,\nHuman Resources Department','READING','Part 6 - Passage 009 (Job Application Follow-up)',NULL),(160,NULL,NULL,6,'To: All Authorized Drivers\nFrom: Fleet Management Department\nSubject: Updated Guidelines for Company Vehicle Usage\n\nThis memo outlines the updated guidelines for the use of company-owned vehicles. Adherence to these rules is ------- (37) ------- for all employees authorized to operate company vehicles.\n\nFirstly, all vehicles must be used for business purposes only, unless prior authorization for personal use has been granted. Drivers are responsible for ensuring the vehicle is kept clean and in good working ------- (38) -------. Any mechanical issues or damage must be reported to the Fleet Management department immediately. ------- (39) -------.\n\nFurthermore, all drivers must possess a valid driver\'s license and adhere to all traffic laws. Fuel cards are provided for refueling and should be used ------- (40) -------. Personal use of fuel cards is strictly prohibited.\n\nFailure to comply with these guidelines may result in disciplinary action.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 010 (Memo: Company Vehicle Guidelines)',NULL),(161,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Important Update: New Version of ConnectPro Software Now Available!\n\nDear ConnectPro User,\n\nWe are thrilled to announce the release of ConnectPro Version 3.0! This latest update includes a range of new features and improvements ------- (41) ------- to enhance your productivity and user experience.\n\nKey enhancements include a redesigned user interface for easier navigation, faster processing speeds, and improved security protocols. ------- (42) -------. We have also added several new collaboration tools based on valuable feedback from users like you. To learn more about these new features, please visit the \"What\'s New\" section on our website or view the tutorial videos ------- (43) ------- in the help section.\n\nUpdating to Version 3.0 is highly recommended for all users to benefit from these advancements. The update is free and can be downloaded directly from your ConnectPro dashboard. Thank you for being a ------- (44) ------- ConnectPro customer.\n\nThe ConnectPro Team','READING','Part 6 - Passage 011 (Software Update Advertisement)',NULL),(162,NULL,NULL,6,'In today\'s competitive market, customer feedback is more important than ever. Actively seeking and responding to customer opinions can provide businesses with ------- (45) ------- insights into their products, services, and overall customer experience.\n\nCompanies that prioritize customer feedback often see improvements in customer loyalty and retention. ------- (46) -------. Furthermore, negative feedback, while sometimes difficult to hear, can highlight critical areas needing improvement and can be a catalyst for ------- (47) ------- innovation.\n\nThere are various methods for collecting feedback, such as surveys, online reviews, and direct customer interactions. Regardless of the method used, the key is to analyze the information received and take ------- (48) ------- action to address concerns and make necessary adjustments.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 012 (Article: Customer Feedback)',NULL),(163,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: You\'re Invited! Annual Tech Innovators Networking Event\n\nDear [Name],\n\nWe are delighted to invite you to our Annual Tech Innovators Networking Event on Thursday, September 25th, from 6:00 PM to 9:00 PM at the Grand City Ballroom. This event provides a unique ------- (49) ------- for professionals in the technology sector to connect, share ideas, and explore potential collaborations.\n\nThe evening will feature a keynote address by renowned tech entrepreneur, Ms. Evelyn Reed, followed by an open networking session. ------- (50) -------. Light refreshments and beverages will be served throughout the evening. We believe this event will be an invaluable resource for anyone looking to ------- (51) ------- their professional network and stay abreast of industry trends.\n\nAttendance is free, but pre-registration is required as space is limited. Please RSVP by September 18th via the link provided below. We sincerely hope you can ------- (52) ------- us for what promises to be an inspiring and productive evening.\n\nWarm regards,\nThe Event Organizing Committee','READING','Part 6 - Passage 013 (Networking Event Invitation)',NULL),(164,NULL,NULL,7,'Subject: Inquiry about Conference Room Booking\nTo: events@cityconventioncenter.com\nFrom: sarah.chen@techsolutions.com\nDate: June 2, 2025\n\nDear Sir/Madam,\n\nI am writing on behalf of TechSolutions Inc. to inquire about the availability of your conference rooms for a one-day corporate event we are planning in August. We anticipate approximately 80-100 attendees.\n\nWe would require a room equipped with a projector, a sound system, and reliable Wi-Fi access. Catering services for lunch and two coffee breaks would also be needed. Could you please provide us with information regarding your room options, rates, and catering packages? Additionally, we would like to know if there is on-site parking available for our guests.\n\nOur preferred date is August 15th, but we are flexible and can consider other dates in mid-August if necessary.\n\nThank you for your time and assistance. We look forward to your prompt reply.\n\nSincerely,\nSarah Chen\nEvent Coordinator, TechSolutions Inc.','READING','Part 7 - Passage 001 (Email - Information Request)',NULL),(165,NULL,NULL,7,'**Sparkle Cleaners - Your Professional Cleaning Solution!**\n\nTired of spending your weekends cleaning? Let Sparkle Cleaners handle the work for you! We offer a comprehensive range of residential and commercial cleaning services tailored to meet your specific needs. Our experienced and insured team uses eco-friendly products to ensure a safe and healthy environment for your family or employees.\n\nServices include:\n* Standard home cleaning (dusting, vacuuming, mopping)\n* Deep cleaning services\n* Office and commercial space cleaning\n* Move-in/move-out cleaning\n\n**Special Offer for New Customers:** Get 20% off your first cleaning service!\nCall us today at 555-0199 or visit www.sparklecleaners.com to get a free, no-obligation quote. We are available Monday to Saturday, from 8 AM to 6 PM. Let us make your space sparkle!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 002 (Service Advertisement)',NULL),(166,NULL,NULL,7,'MEMORANDUM\n\nTo: All Department Heads\nFrom: Susan Choi, Director of Operations\nDate: June 3, 2025\nSubject: Update to Travel Expense Reimbursement Policy\n\nThis memo is to inform you of an important update to our company’s travel expense reimbursement policy, effective July 1, 2025. These changes are being implemented to streamline the reimbursement process and ensure better cost management.\n\nKey changes include:\n1.  All travel expense reports must now be submitted within 15 days of travel completion, reduced from the previous 30-day limit.\n2.  Original itemized receipts are required for all expenses exceeding $25. Digital copies will only be accepted for expenses under this amount if an original is not obtainable.\n3.  The mileage reimbursement rate for personal vehicle use on company business will be adjusted to $0.58 per mile, reflecting current federal guidelines.\n\nWe understand that policy changes can require an adjustment period. Therefore, training sessions will be held next week to explain these updates in detail and answer any questions. A schedule for these sessions will be circulated by end of day tomorrow. Please ensure all employees in your respective departments are made aware of these changes and encouraged to attend a training session.\n\nYour cooperation in adhering to this updated policy is greatly appreciated.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 003 (Internal Memo - Policy Change)',NULL),(167,NULL,NULL,7,'**Local Bookstore Celebrates 25th Anniversary**\n\nOakhaven Books, a beloved independent bookstore in downtown Oakhaven, is celebrating its 25th anniversary this month. Founded by Eleanor Vance in 1999, the store has become a community hub, known for its curated selection of books, cozy atmosphere, and knowledgeable staff.\n\nTo mark this significant milestone, Oakhaven Books will be hosting a series of special events throughout June. These include author signings, children’s story hours, and a 25% discount on all hardcover books during the anniversary week (June 15-21). Ms. Vance stated, \"We are incredibly grateful for the support our community has shown us over the past quarter-century. This celebration is our way of saying thank you.\"\n\nThe store also plans to launch an online ordering system by the end of the year, a move aimed at reaching a wider audience while still maintaining its commitment to personalized service.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 004 (Short News Article)',NULL),(168,NULL,NULL,7,'**Community Cleanup Day - Saturday, July 12th**\n\nJoin your neighbors for a Community Cleanup Day on Saturday, July 12th, from 9:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Let\'s work together to make our town even more beautiful!\n\nWe will meet at the Town Hall Square. Volunteers will be provided with gloves, trash bags, and safety vests. Tasks will include picking up litter from parks, streets, and a section of the riverbank. Light refreshments and water will be available for all participants.\n\nThis is a great opportunity to contribute to our community and meet new people. Families are welcome, but children under 12 must be accompanied by an adult.\n\nTo sign up as a volunteer or for more information, please contact Maria Sanchez at msanchez@oakhavencommunity.org or call 555-0234 by July 5th. Your help can make a big difference!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 005 (Community Event Notice)',NULL),(169,NULL,NULL,7,'**Mark (10:05 AM):** Hi Lisa, are you still planning to attend the marketing workshop this afternoon? It starts at 2 PM.\n**Lisa (10:07 AM):** Hi Mark! Yes, I am. I just need to finish up this report first. It\'s taking longer than I expected.\n**Mark (10:08 AM):** Okay, no problem. Do you want me to save you a seat? It might get crowded.\n**Lisa (10:10 AM):** That would be great, thanks! I should be there around 1:50 PM, hopefully. I\'ll text you if I\'m running late.\n**Mark (10:11 AM):** Sounds good. I\'ll grab a seat near the front for us. See you later!\n**Lisa (10:12 AM):** Perfect, thanks again! See ya.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 006 (Text Message Chain)',NULL),(170,NULL,NULL,7,'MEMORANDUM\n\nTo: All Staff\nFrom: Management\nDate: October 28, 2025\nSubject: Adjustment to Winter Office Hours\n\nPlease be informed that, effective November 10, 2025, our company\'s standard office hours will be adjusted for the winter season. The new office hours will be from 8:30 AM to 5:00 PM, Monday through Friday. This change reflects a 30-minute earlier start and finish time compared to our current summer schedule of 9:00 AM to 5:30 PM.\n\nThis adjustment is being made to better align with daylight hours during the winter months and to accommodate employee requests for an earlier end to the workday. We believe this change will also contribute to energy savings for the company.\n\nAll employees are expected to adhere to the new schedule. Department heads are responsible for ensuring that their teams are aware of this change and that operational needs are met. Please adjust your personal schedules accordingly.\n\nIf you have any questions regarding this change, please contact the Human Resources department.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 007 (Memo - Office Hour Change)',NULL),(171,NULL,NULL,7,'Mr. James Harrison\nCustomer Service Manager\nElectroGadgets Inc.\n123 Tech Park Avenue\nInnoville, CA 90210\n\nDear Mr. Harrison,\n\nI am writing to express my dissatisfaction with a product I recently purchased from your online store, order #INV78901, on May 15, 2025. The item in question is the \"ProSound X20\" wireless headphones.\n\nUpon receiving the headphones on May 20th, I found that the right earpiece was not functioning at all. I followed all troubleshooting steps provided in the manual, including fully charging the device and attempting to re-pair it with multiple audio sources, but the issue persists. This is very disappointing, as I was looking forward to using this product.\n\nI have attached a copy of my purchase receipt and a short video demonstrating the malfunction. I would appreciate it if you could arrange for a replacement unit to be sent to me or provide instructions for returning the defective item for a full refund. I hope for a prompt resolution to this matter.\n\nThank you for your attention to this issue.\n\nSincerely,\nLaura Chen\n(555) 123-4567\nlaura.chen@email.com','READING','Part 7 - Passage 008 (Formal Letter - Service Complaint)',NULL),(172,NULL,NULL,7,'**TechForward Conference - Day 1 Schedule**\n**Location: Grand Convention Hall**\n**Date: November 5, 2025**\n\n| Time          | Activity                                      | Speaker/Location   |\n|---------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------------|\n| 8:00 - 9:00 AM| Registration & Welcome Coffee                 | Lobby              |\n| 9:00 - 9:15 AM| Opening Remarks                               | Main Auditorium    |\n| 9:15 - 10:30 AM| Keynote Address: The Future of AI             | Dr. Emily Carter   |\n| 10:30 - 11:00 AM| Coffee Break & Networking                   | Exhibition Hall    |\n| 11:00 AM - 12:30 PM| Concurrent Sessions:                      |                    |\n|               | - AI in Healthcare                            | Room A             |\n|               | - Machine Learning Innovations                | Room B             |\n|               | - Ethics in Artificial Intelligence           | Room C             |\n| 12:30 - 1:30 PM| Lunch Break                                   | Cafeteria          |\n| 1:30 - 3:00 PM | Panel Discussion: AI Start-up Challenges      | Main Auditorium    |\n| 3:00 - 3:30 PM | Afternoon Tea                                 | Exhibition Hall    |\n| 3:30 - 5:00 PM | Workshop: Building Your First AI Application  | Room A (Limited Seats) |\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 009 (Workshop Schedule)',NULL),(173,NULL,NULL,7,'**Product Review: The Nova Smartwatch**\nReviewer: TechGuru101\nRating: 4.5 / 5 stars\n\nI\'ve been using the Nova Smartwatch for about a month now, and I\'m thoroughly impressed. The setup was incredibly easy, and it synced seamlessly with my smartphone. The battery life is a standout feature – I can easily get two full days of use on a single charge, even with regular GPS tracking during my runs.\n\nThe display is bright and easy to read, even in direct sunlight. I particularly enjoy the wide range of fitness tracking options, from step counting to heart rate monitoring and sleep analysis. The built-in GPS is accurate and a great addition for outdoor activities. My only minor complaint is that the selection of third-party apps is still somewhat limited compared to other smartwatches on the market. However, the core functionalities are excellent, and the watch itself feels premium and well-built.\n\nOverall, I highly recommend the Nova Smartwatch for anyone looking for a reliable, feature-rich, and stylish wearable device with excellent battery life.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 010 (Web Page - Product Review)',NULL),(174,NULL,NULL,7,'Subject: Meeting Confirmation: Project Phoenix Review\nTo: Project Phoenix Team\nFrom: Angela Merkel, Project Manager\nDate: June 4, 2025\n\nDear Team,\n\nThis email is to confirm our upcoming meeting to review the progress of Project Phoenix.\nDate: Friday, June 6, 2025\nTime: 10:00 AM - 11:30 AM\nLocation: Conference Room 3B\n\nThe main agenda items for this meeting will be:\n1.  Review of milestones achieved in May.\n2.  Discussion of current challenges and roadblocks.\n3.  Planning for tasks scheduled for June and July.\n4.  Budget allocation review for Q3.\n\nPlease come prepared to discuss your team\'s specific contributions and any concerns you may have. All relevant documents and progress reports should be uploaded to the shared drive by end of day Thursday, June 5th. This will allow everyone to review the materials beforehand.\n\nIf you are unable to attend, please notify me as soon as possible.\n\nThank you,\nAngela Merkel','READING','Part 7 - Passage 011 (Email - Meeting Confirmation)',NULL),(175,NULL,NULL,7,'**Learn a New Language with LinguaBoost!**\n\nUnlock your potential with LinguaBoost, the revolutionary software designed to make language learning fast, fun, and effective. Whether you\'re a beginner or looking to polish your skills, LinguaBoost offers personalized learning paths tailored to your level and goals.\n\n**Why Choose LinguaBoost?**\n* **Interactive Lessons:** Engaging exercises, real-life conversation simulations, and speech recognition technology to perfect your pronunciation.\n* **Flexible Learning:** Study anytime, anywhere with our mobile app and offline mode.\n* **Track Your Progress:** Monitor your achievements with detailed statistics and personalized feedback.\n* **Wide Range of Languages:** Choose from over 20 languages, including Spanish, French, German, Mandarin, and Japanese.\n\n**Special Launch Offer:** Sign up this month and get your first 3 months for the price of 1! Plus, receive a free e-book on effective language learning strategies.\nVisit www.linguaboost.com to start your free trial today!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 012 (Language Learning Software Ad)',NULL),(176,NULL,NULL,7,'**Public Library - Holiday Hours Notification**\n\nPlease note the following changes to the Oakhaven Public Library hours during the upcoming national holiday period:\n\n* **Friday, July 4th (Independence Day):** CLOSED\n* **Saturday, July 5th:** Open 10:00 AM - 2:00 PM (Reduced Hours)\n* **Sunday, July 6th:** CLOSED\n* **Monday, July 7th:** Regular hours resume (9:00 AM - 8:00 PM)\n\nOur online resources, including e-books, audiobooks, and databases, will remain accessible 24/7 via our website at www.oakhavenlibrary.org. The book drop will be available for returns throughout the holiday period.\n\nWe apologize for any inconvenience these changes may cause and wish everyone a safe and enjoyable holiday. Please plan your library visits accordingly.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 013 (Notice - Library Holiday Hours)',NULL),(177,NULL,NULL,7,'**The Growing Importance of Corporate Wellness Programs**\n\nIn recent years, an increasing number of companies have recognized the value of investing in corporate wellness programs. These initiatives, which can range from on-site fitness centers and health screenings to stress management workshops and nutritional counseling, offer significant benefits for both employees and employers.\n\nStudies have shown that employees participating in wellness programs tend to report higher job satisfaction, improved morale, and reduced stress levels. This, in turn, can lead to increased productivity and lower rates of absenteeism. For employers, the return on investment can be seen in decreased healthcare costs and an enhanced corporate image, making the company more attractive to potential talent. While implementing a comprehensive wellness program requires an initial outlay, the long-term advantages often outweigh the costs.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 014 (Article - Corporate Wellness)',NULL),(178,NULL,NULL,7,'**Modern Business Today - Subscription Form**\n\nPlease fill out the form below to subscribe to Modern Business Today magazine.\n\n**Subscriber Information:**\nFull Name: _________________________\nCompany: _________________________ (Optional)\nMailing Address: ____________________ Street, ____________________ City, ________ State, ________ Zip Code\nEmail Address: _________________________\n\n**Subscription Options (Select one):**\n[ ] 1 Year (12 Issues) - $59.99\n[ ] 2 Years (24 Issues) - $99.99 (Save 20%!)\n[ ] Digital Only (1 Year) - $39.99\n\n**Payment Method:**\n[ ] Credit Card (Visa, MasterCard, Amex)\nCard Number: _________________________\nExpiration Date (MM/YY): _______ / _______\nCVV: _______\n[ ] Check (Payable to \"Modern Business Today\")\n\n*For international subscriptions, please add $20 per year for shipping.\n*Allow 4-6 weeks for the first issue to arrive for print subscriptions.\n*Digital access is immediate upon payment confirmation.\n\nSubmit this form with payment to: Subscriptions, Modern Business Today, P.O. Box 123, New York, NY 10001.\nOr subscribe online at www.modernbusinesstoday.com/subscribe.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 015 (Magazine Subscription Form - Textual)',NULL),(179,NULL,NULL,7,'**Anna (Monday, 9:30 AM):** Hi Ben, are you free for lunch sometime this week? I wanted to discuss the new marketing proposal with you.\n**Ben (Monday, 9:32 AM):** Hi Anna! Good idea. This week is a bit busy for me. How about Thursday or Friday?\n**Anna (Monday, 9:33 AM):** Thursday works for me. Around 12:30 PM?\n**Ben (Monday, 9:35 AM):** Perfect. There\'s that new Italian place near the office, \"Pasta Paradise.\" Want to try it?\n**Anna (Monday, 9:36 AM):** Sounds delicious! Let\'s do that. So, Thursday at 12:30 PM at Pasta Paradise.\n**Ben (Monday, 9:37 AM):** Confirmed. Looking forward to it!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 016 (Text Messages - Arranging Lunch)',NULL),(180,NULL,NULL,7,'MEMORANDUM\n\nTo: All Hiring Managers\nFrom: Human Resources Department\nDate: July 8, 2025\nSubject: Enhancements to New Employee Onboarding Process\n\nTo ensure a smoother and more effective integration of new hires into our company culture and their respective roles, we are introducing several enhancements to our onboarding process, effective August 1st.\n\nThe revised process will include a more structured first-week schedule, featuring dedicated time for HR orientation, IT setup and training, and an introductory meeting with their assigned mentor. Mentors will play a crucial role in guiding new employees during their initial months. Additionally, a comprehensive digital onboarding kit will be provided prior to the new employee\'s start date, containing essential company information, policy documents, and an overview of their first-week activities.\n\nWe believe these changes will help new employees feel more welcomed, prepared, and quickly become productive members of our team. Department managers are requested to work closely with HR to ensure all new hires starting on or after August 1st experience this updated process. Feedback on the new process will be collected after the first quarter of implementation.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 017 (Memo - New Employee Onboarding)',NULL),(181,NULL,NULL,7,'GreenScape Landscaping Services\n45 Garden Lane, Springfield\n\nJune 5, 2025\n\nMs. Emily Carter\n789 Willow Creek Drive\nSpringfield\n\nDear Ms. Carter,\n\nOn behalf of the entire team at GreenScape Landscaping Services, I would like to extend our sincere gratitude for choosing us to design and implement the new garden for your beautiful home. We truly enjoyed working with you on this project and are thrilled with the final outcome.\n\nYour vision for a tranquil, low-maintenance garden with native plants was a wonderful inspiration for our design team. We are particularly pleased with how the stone pathway زیبایی and the new water feature complement the existing architecture of your house.\n\nWe strive to provide the highest quality service and craftsmanship, and your satisfaction is our top priority. We hope your new garden brings you many years of enjoyment. Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have any questions or require any future landscaping services.\n\nThank you once again for your business.\n\nSincerely,\nDavid Lee\nOwner, GreenScape Landscaping Services\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 018 (Letter - Thank You Note)',NULL),(182,NULL,NULL,7,'**Itinerary: Ms. Sandra Bell - Chicago Sales Trip**\n**Dates: July 14 - July 16, 2025**\n\n**Monday, July 14:**\n* 9:00 AM: Depart from New York (JFK) - Flight AA123\n* 10:30 AM (CT): Arrive in Chicago (ORD)\n* 11:30 AM: Check into Hotel Grand Chicago\n* 1:00 PM: Lunch meeting with Mr. Robert Davis ( потенциальных клиентов )\n* 3:00 PM - 5:00 PM: Client Presentations at Davis Corp.\n* 7:00 PM: Dinner with regional sales team\n\n**Tuesday, July 15:**\n* 9:30 AM: Meeting with Apex Industries (New Lead)\n* 12:00 PM: Working Lunch - Prepare for afternoon session\n* 2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Product Demonstration at TechGlobal Solutions\n* 6:00 PM: Networking event at Chicago Business Hub\n\n**Wednesday, July 16:**\n* 10:00 AM: Follow-up meeting with Davis Corp.\n* 1:00 PM: Lunch and debrief with Chicago office manager\n* 4:00 PM: Depart from Chicago (ORD) - Flight AA456\n* 7:30 PM (ET): Arrive in New York (JFK)\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 019 (Business Trip Itinerary)',NULL),(183,NULL,NULL,7,'**Frequently Asked Questions - SwiftShip Delivery Services**\n\n**Q1: What are your standard delivery times?**\nA1: For domestic shipments within the same city, we offer same-day delivery if booked before 12 PM. For intercity domestic shipments, standard delivery is typically 1-3 business days. International delivery times vary greatly depending on the destination and customs procedures.\n\n**Q2: Can I track my package?**\nA2: Yes, all shipments sent via SwiftShip can be tracked in real-time. Once your package is dispatched, you will receive a tracking number via email and SMS. You can use this number on our website or mobile app to monitor your package\'s progress.\n\n**Q3: What items are prohibited from shipping?**\nA3: For a full list of prohibited items, please refer to Section 4 of our Terms and Conditions page on our website. Generally, this includes hazardous materials, perishable goods without proper packaging, illegal substances, and live animals.\n\n**Q4: What if my package is lost or damaged?**\nA4: SwiftShip provides insurance coverage for all shipments up to a certain value. In the unfortunate event of a lost or damaged package, please contact our Customer Service hotline within 7 days of the expected delivery date to initiate a claim. You will need to provide your tracking number and proof of value.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 020 (Web Page - FAQ)',NULL),(184,NULL,NULL,7,'Subject: Leave of Absence Request - Mark Olsen\nTo: Ms. Sarah Jennings, Department Manager\nFrom: Mark Olsen, Senior Analyst\nDate: June 5, 2025\n\nDear Ms. Jennings,\n\nI am writing to formally request a leave of absence for a period of two weeks, from Monday, July 7, 2025, to Friday, July 18, 2025, inclusive. I plan to return to work on Monday, July 21, 2025.\n\nThe reason for this request is to attend to a personal family matter that requires my presence overseas. I understand the importance of my current projects, particularly Project Titan, and I have already taken steps to ensure a smooth workflow during my absence. I have prepared a detailed handover document for my colleague, Emily White, who has kindly agreed to cover my urgent responsibilities. I will also complete all critical tasks and reports due before my departure.\n\nI will have limited access to email during this period but will endeavor to check for any urgent messages periodically. I would be grateful if you could approve my request. Please let me know if there is any further information or documentation required from my side.\n\nThank you for your consideration.\n\nSincerely,\nMark Olsen','READING','Part 7 - Passage 021 (Email - Leave Request)',NULL),(185,NULL,NULL,7,'**The Corner Bistro - Your Neighborhood Favorite!**\n\nExperience delightful dining at The Corner Bistro, conveniently located at 12 Oak Street. We pride ourselves on serving fresh, locally-sourced ingredients in a cozy and welcoming atmosphere. Our menu features a variety of classic American dishes with a modern twist, alongside a carefully selected wine list.\n\n**This Week\'s Specials (June 2nd - June 8th):**\n* Monday: Half-price appetizers\n* Wednesday: \"Wine Wednesday\" - 25% off all bottles of wine\n* Friday: Live Jazz Music from 7 PM to 10 PM\n\n**Happy Hour:** Monday - Friday, 4 PM to 6 PM. Enjoy discounted drinks and small plates!\n\nWhether you\'re looking for a casual lunch, a romantic dinner, or a place to unwind with friends, The Corner Bistro is the perfect spot. Reservations are recommended, especially on weekends. Call us at 555-0345 or book online at www.cornerbistro.com.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 022 (Local Restaurant Promotion)',NULL),(186,NULL,NULL,7,'**NOTICE TO ALL TENANTS**\n\nSubject: Elevator Maintenance - West Wing\n\nPlease be advised that the elevators in the West Wing of the City Central Tower will be temporarily out of service for scheduled maintenance. This work is essential to ensure the continued safe and reliable operation of the elevators.\n\n**Maintenance Period:**\n* Start Date: Monday, June 9, 2025, at 9:00 AM\n* End Date: Wednesday, June 11, 2025, at 5:00 PM (approximately)\n\nDuring this period, tenants and visitors in the West Wing are advised to use the stairwells or the elevators located in the East Wing. Signage will be posted to direct you to the nearest alternative access.\n\nWe understand that this may cause some inconvenience and appreciate your patience and cooperation as we work to improve our building facilities. For any urgent accessibility concerns, please contact Building Management at extension 5000.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 023 (Notice - Office Building Maintenance)',NULL),(187,NULL,NULL,7,'**The Shift Towards Renewable Energy Sources**\n\nThe global energy landscape is undergoing a significant transformation, with a notable shift towards renewable energy sources such as solar, wind, and hydropower. This transition is driven by several factors, including growing concerns about climate change, advancements in renewable technologies, and decreasing costs of implementation. Governments worldwide are also playing a crucial role by setting ambitious renewable energy targets and offering incentives for green energy projects.\n\nOne of the most rapidly expanding sectors is solar power. The cost of solar panels has plummeted in the last decade, making it an increasingly competitive option compared to traditional fossil fuels. Wind energy is also experiencing substantial growth, particularly in regions with favorable wind conditions. While hydropower remains a major contributor, its expansion potential is often limited by geographical and environmental considerations.\n\nDespite the positive momentum, challenges remain. Grid integration of intermittent renewable sources and the need for large-scale energy storage solutions are key technical hurdles that need to be addressed to ensure a stable and reliable energy supply.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 024 (Article - Renewable Energy Trends)',NULL),(188,NULL,NULL,7,'**Product Warranty Registration - Aura Electronics**\n\nThank you for purchasing an Aura Electronics product! To activate your warranty, please complete and submit this form within 30 days of purchase.\n\n**Product Information:**\nModel Number: _______________ (Located on product packaging or device)\nSerial Number: _______________ (Located on product packaging or device)\nDate of Purchase (MM/DD/YYYY): ____/____/____\nPlace of Purchase (Store Name/Website): ____________________\n\n**Customer Information:**\nFull Name: _________________________\nAddress: _________________________________________\nEmail: _________________________\nPhone Number: _________________________\n\n[ ] Yes, I would like to receive product updates and special offers from Aura Electronics via email.\n\n**Terms:** This warranty covers manufacturing defects for a period of one (1) year from the date of purchase. It does not cover damage due to misuse, accident, or normal wear and tear. A copy of the original purchase receipt is required for all warranty claims. For full warranty terms and conditions, please visit www.auraelectronics.com/warranty.\n\nSubmit online at www.auraelectronics.com/register or mail to:\nAura Electronics Warranty Dept., P.O. Box 789, Tech City, TX 75001.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 025 (Warranty Registration Form - Textual)',NULL),(189,NULL,NULL,7,'**Team Alpha - Project Update**\n\n**Liam (Wed, 2:15 PM):** Hey team, just checking in on the presentation slides. Sarah, how\'s the market research section coming along?\n**Sarah (Wed, 2:17 PM):** Hi Liam, nearly done! I should have the final stats compiled by end of day. Just verifying a few sources.\n**Mike (Wed, 2:18 PM):** I\'ve finished the competitor analysis slides. I can send them over to you, Liam, to integrate.\n**Liam (Wed, 2:19 PM):** Great, Mike! Send them when ready. Sarah, let me know if you need any help with the data.\n**Sarah (Wed, 2:20 PM):** Thanks, Liam! I think I\'m good for now. My main concern is getting the visuals to look consistent with Mike\'s section.\n**Mike (Wed, 2:21 PM):** I used the standard company template, Sarah. Font: Arial 12pt, color scheme blue/grey. Should be easy to match.\n**Liam (Wed, 2:23 PM):** Excellent. Let\'s aim to have a draft of the full presentation ready for review by Friday morning.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 026 (Text Messages - Group Project)',NULL),(190,NULL,NULL,7,'MEMORANDUM\n\nTo: All Employees\nFrom: Human Resources Department\nDate: August 1, 2025\nSubject: Updated Company Dress Code Policy\n\nEffective August 15, 2025, an updated dress code policy will be implemented across all departments of Innovate Corp. This revision aims to maintain a professional image while allowing for more comfort and flexibility.\n\nThe new policy categorizes dress standards into \"Business Professional\" for client-facing roles and meetings, and \"Business Casual\" for general office days. \"Business Professional\" includes suits, dress shirts, ties (for men), blouses, and appropriate skirts or trousers. \"Business Casual\" allows for more relaxed attire such as khakis, polo shirts, and sweaters, but T-shirts with large logos, jeans with rips, and athletic wear remain inappropriate for the workplace.\n\nFridays will be designated as \"Casual Fridays,\" where clean, smart jeans and company-branded T-shirts are permissible. However, even on Casual Fridays, attire should always be neat, clean, and appropriate for a professional environment. Detailed guidelines with visual examples will be available on the company intranet by August 5th.\n\nWe trust that all employees will use their best judgment in adhering to this updated policy.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 027 (Memo - New Dress Code Policy)',NULL),(191,NULL,NULL,7,'15 Riverview Terrace\nSpringdale, IL 60504\nJune 7, 2025\n\nBilling Department\nConnectNet ISP\nP.O. Box 5000\nSpringdale, IL 60505\n\nSubject: Billing Error - Account #789-12345\n\nDear Sir/Madam,\n\nI am writing to report a billing error on my recent internet service statement dated June 1, 2025, for account #789-12345. My current plan is the \"Basic Home Internet\" package at $49.99 per month. However, the latest statement shows a charge of $79.99.\n\nI have been a loyal customer for over three years and have always paid my bills on time. I did not authorize any changes to my service plan, nor was I notified of any price increase that would account for this $30 discrepancy. I believe this is an error and request that it be corrected promptly.\n\nCould you please investigate this matter and adjust my bill to reflect the correct amount of $49.99? I have enclosed a copy of the statement in question and my previous month\'s bill for your reference. I would appreciate a confirmation once this issue has been resolved.\n\nThank you for your immediate attention to this problem.\n\nSincerely,\nDavid Choi\n(555) 987-6543\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 028 (Letter - Billing Error Complaint)',NULL),(192,NULL,NULL,7,'**Historic City Walking Tour - Itinerary**\n**Tour Guide: Johnathan Pierce | Duration: 3 hours**\n\n* **10:00 AM:** Meet at City Hall steps. Introduction and overview of the tour.\n* **10:15 AM:** Depart City Hall. Walk along Main Street, discussing its historical significance and architecture.\n* **11:00 AM:** Visit St. Michael\'s Cathedral (Exterior view and brief history).\n* **11:45 AM:** Arrive at the Old Market Square. Explore local vendor stalls. (20-minute break for refreshments/shopping)\n* **12:05 PM:** Continue to the Heritage Museum.\n* **12:30 PM - 1:00 PM:** Guided tour of selected exhibits within the Heritage Museum.\n* **1:00 PM:** Tour concludes at the Heritage Museum exit.\n\n**Notes:**\n* Please wear comfortable walking shoes.\n* The tour will proceed rain or shine, so please dress appropriately for the weather.\n* No food or drink is allowed inside St. Michael\'s Cathedral or the Heritage Museum.\n* Restrooms are available at City Hall, Old Market Square, and the Heritage Museum.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 029 (Sightseeing Tour Itinerary)',NULL),(193,NULL,NULL,7,'**About BrightFuture Solutions**\n\nFounded in 2010, BrightFuture Solutions is a leading provider of innovative educational software for K-12 schools. Our mission is to empower educators and engage students through cutting-edge technology and research-backed pedagogical approaches. We believe that technology, when used effectively, can transform the learning experience and help students achieve their full potential.\n\nOur flagship product, \"LearnSmart Suite,\" offers interactive modules in mathematics, science, and language arts, tailored to various grade levels. It incorporates gamification elements and personalized learning paths to keep students motivated and challenged. We work closely with teachers and curriculum developers to ensure our software aligns with educational standards and meets the real-world needs of today\'s classrooms.\n\nHeadquartered in Austin, Texas, BrightFuture Solutions is committed to ongoing innovation and customer support. We offer comprehensive training for educators and dedicated technical assistance to ensure seamless integration of our products into school systems. Our vision is to be a global leader in educational technology.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 030 (Web Page - About Us)',NULL),(194,NULL,NULL,7,'Subject: Invitation: Advanced Excel Skills Training\nTo: All Marketing Department Staff\nFrom: hr_training@innovatech.com\nDate: June 6, 2025\n\nDear Marketing Team,\n\nThe Human Resources Department is pleased to invite you to an upcoming training session on Advanced Excel Skills. This session is specifically designed to help you enhance your data analysis and reporting capabilities using Microsoft Excel.\n\n**Date:** Wednesday, June 18, 2025\n**Time:** 9:00 AM - 4:00 PM (with a one-hour lunch break)\n**Location:** Training Room C, 3rd Floor\n**Instructor:** Ms. Laura Bellweather, Certified Microsoft Trainer\n\nTopics covered will include advanced formulas, pivot tables, data visualization techniques, and macro basics. This hands-on workshop will provide practical exercises to ensure you can apply these skills directly to your daily tasks. We believe this training will significantly improve your efficiency and the quality of your marketing reports.\n\nSpaces are limited to 20 participants to ensure personalized attention. Please register by June 12th via the internal training portal (link: [Internal Portal Link]).\n\nWe encourage all interested team members to take advantage of this valuable learning opportunity.\n\nSincerely,\nThe HR Training Team','READING','Part 7 - Passage 031 (Email - Training Invitation)',NULL),(195,NULL,NULL,7,'**Introducing the new AquaPure Home Water Filter!**\n\nTired of plastic water bottles? Make the switch to a sustainable solution with the AquaPure Home Water Filter. Our innovative filter attaches directly to your faucet, providing clean, great-tasting water while reducing plastic waste.\n\n**Key Features:**\n* Advanced 5-stage filtration system removes 99% of common contaminants.\n* Easy to install – no tools required!\n* Long-lasting filter cartridge (up to 3 months or 100 gallons).\n* Sleek, modern design that complements any kitchen decor.\n* Made from recycled and BPA-free materials.\n\n**Special Introductory Offer:** For a limited time, purchase the AquaPure Home Water Filter starter kit and receive two bonus filter cartridges FREE (a $30 value)! This offer is valid until July 31st or while supplies last.\n\nOrder yours today at www.aquapurefilters.com and join us in making a difference for our planet!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 032 (Advertisement - Eco-Friendly Product)',NULL),(196,NULL,NULL,7,'**Public Notice: Temporary Road Closure - Downtown Festival**\n\nThe City of Oakhaven Department of Transportation wishes to inform residents and businesses of a temporary road closure to facilitate the annual Oakhaven Summer Festival.\n\n**Affected Area:** Main Street, between Elm Avenue and Oak Street.\n**Date of Closure:** Saturday, July 19, 2025\n**Time of Closure:** 8:00 AM to 10:00 PM\n\nDuring this period, the specified section of Main Street will be closed to all vehicular traffic. Pedestrian access will be maintained. Detour routes will be clearly marked, and traffic officers will be on site to assist with directing traffic. Local businesses on Main Street within the closed zone will remain open and accessible to pedestrians.\n\nParking restrictions will also be in effect in the surrounding areas. Please observe all posted signage. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause and thank you for your cooperation in making this community event a success. For more information, please visit the city website at www.oakhavencity.gov/events.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 033 (Notice - Temporary Road Closure)',NULL),(197,NULL,NULL,7,'**Rethinking Urban Mobility: The Future of City Transport**\n\nAs cities around the world continue to grow, urban transportation systems face increasing pressure. Traffic congestion, air pollution, and the demand for more sustainable options are driving innovation in how we move around metropolitan areas. Experts predict a future where personal car ownership in dense city centers becomes less common, replaced by a diverse mix of shared mobility services.\n\nThese services include ride-hailing apps, bike-sharing programs, and electric scooter rentals, all integrated with vastly improved public transit networks. The development of autonomous (self-driving) vehicles is also poised to play a significant role, potentially revolutionizing logistics and personal transport. Furthermore, smart city technologies will enable better traffic management and provide real-time information to commuters, making journeys more efficient.\n\nThe transition will not be without its challenges, including regulatory hurdles, infrastructure investment, and ensuring equitable access for all residents. However, the potential benefits – cleaner air, less congested streets, and more livable cities – are substantial.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 034 (Article - Urban Transportation)',NULL),(198,NULL,NULL,7,'**Customer Satisfaction Survey - QuickByte Cafe**\n\nThank you for dining at QuickByte Cafe! Please take a few moments to complete this survey. Your feedback is valuable to us.\n\n**Date of Visit:** _______________\n**Time of Visit:** _______________\n\n**Please rate the following on a scale of 1 (Poor) to 5 (Excellent):**\n1.  Quality of Food: [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]\n2.  Speed of Service: [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]\n3.  Friendliness of Staff: [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]\n4.  Cleanliness of Cafe: [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]\n5.  Overall Experience: [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]\n\n**What did you like most about your visit?**\n____________________________________________________\n\n**How could we improve your experience?**\n____________________________________________________\n\n[ ] Yes, I would like to be contacted about future promotions.\nEmail: _________________________ (Optional)\n\nThank you for your time!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 035 (Customer Satisfaction Survey - Textual)',NULL),(199,NULL,NULL,7,'**Alex (Fri, 6:30 PM):** Hey Chloe, are you free to catch a movie tomorrow night? \"Galactic Heroes 3\" is out.\n**Chloe (Fri, 6:32 PM):** Hi Alex! Oh, I\'d love to, but I already have plans for Saturday evening. What about Sunday?\n**Alex (Fri, 6:33 PM):** Sunday could work. What time are you thinking? There\'s a 7:00 PM show.\n**Chloe (Fri, 6:35 PM):** 7:00 PM on Sunday sounds perfect! Should we meet at the Cityplex Cinema around 6:45 PM?\n**Alex (Fri, 6:36 PM):** Yep, Cityplex is good. I can grab the tickets online beforehand if you like.\n**Chloe (Fri, 6:37 PM):** That would be awesome, thanks! Let me know how much I owe you.\n**Alex (Fri, 6:38 PM):** No worries, my treat this time! See you Sunday.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 036 (Text Messages - Discussing Movie)',NULL),(200,NULL,NULL,7,'MEMORANDUM\n\nTo: All Employees\nFrom: Kendrick Lamar, Human Resources Director\nDate: November 1, 2025\nSubject: Reminder: Annual Performance Review Cycle\n\nThis memo serves as a reminder that the annual performance review cycle for this year is now underway. The review period covers employee performance from January 1, 2025, to October 31, 2025.\n\nAll employees are required to complete their self-assessment forms by November 15th. These forms can be accessed on the HR portal. Following the self-assessment, managers will schedule individual review meetings with their team members between November 20th and December 10th. The purpose of these meetings is to discuss achievements, areas for development, and set goals for the upcoming year.\n\nCompleted and signed review forms must be submitted to Human Resources by December 15th. This process is crucial for professional development, feedback, and considerations for salary adjustments and promotions. We encourage open and constructive dialogue throughout this period.\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 037 (Memo - Performance Reviews)',NULL),(201,NULL,NULL,7,'Children\'s Future Foundation\n789 Hope Avenue, Cityville\n\nOctober 15, 2025\n\nMr. Arthur Pendelton\nCEO, Pendelton Enterprises\n1 Business Plaza, Cityville\n\nDear Mr. Pendelton,\n\nI am writing to you on behalf of the Children\'s Future Foundation, a non-profit organization dedicated to providing educational resources and support to underprivileged children in our community. For over 20 years, we have been committed to helping children achieve their full potential through after-school programs, tutoring services, and scholarship opportunities.\n\nThis year, we are launching a new initiative called \"Tech for Tots,\" aiming to equip local community centers with computers and internet access for young learners. We believe that digital literacy is crucial in today\'s world, and this program will help bridge the digital divide for many children.\n\nWe would be immensely grateful if Pendelton Enterprises would consider becoming a corporate sponsor for our \"Tech for Tots\" initiative. A contribution of any amount would make a significant difference. For example, a $500 donation can provide a refurbished computer, while $2,000 can equip an entire learning station. We have enclosed a detailed proposal outlining sponsorship levels and benefits.\n\nThank you for considering our request. Your support can help shape a brighter future for many children.\n\nSincerely,\nMaria Rodriguez\nDirector, Children\'s Future Foundation\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 038 (Letter - Donation Request)',NULL),(202,NULL,NULL,7,'**Innovatech Conference 2025 - Day 2 Agenda**\n**Theme: Shaping Tomorrow\'s Technology**\n**Date: October 17, 2025**\n\n| Time          | Session Title / Activity                      | Speaker / Room     |\n|---------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------------|\n| 8:30 - 9:00 AM| Morning Coffee & Networking                   | Atrium             |\n| 9:00 - 10:00 AM| Keynote: AI and the Future of Work            | Dr. Lena Hanson / Hall A |\n| 10:00 - 10:15 AM| Short Break                                   |                    |\n| 10:15 - 11:45 AM| Track 1: Cybersecurity Challenges             | Mr. David Choi / Room 101 |\n|               | Track 2: Advances in Cloud Computing          | Ms. Anya Sharma / Room 102 |\n|               | Track 3: The Rise of IoT                      | Dr. Kenji Tanaka / Room 103 |\n| 12:00 - 1:30 PM| Lunch & Expo Visit                            | Grand Ballroom     |\n| 1:30 - 3:00 PM | Workshop: Practical Data Science with Python  | Dr. Lena Hanson / Room 201 |\n|               | Workshop: Agile Project Management            | Ms. Sarah Mills / Room 202 |\n| 3:00 - 3:30 PM | Afternoon Break & Expo Visit                  | Grand Ballroom     |\n| 3:30 - 4:30 PM | Panel: Investing in Tech Startups             | Various / Hall A   |\n| 4:30 PM       | Closing Remarks                               | Hall A             |\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 039 (Conference Schedule - Day 2)',NULL),(203,NULL,NULL,7,'**Careers at TechGen Solutions**\n\nJoin a team that\'s shaping the future of technology! At TechGen Solutions, we foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning. We are always looking for talented and passionate individuals to join our dynamic team.\n\n**Why Work With Us?**\n* **Impactful Work:** Contribute to projects that make a real difference in various industries.\n* **Growth Opportunities:** We invest in our employees\' professional development through training programs, mentorship, and challenging assignments.\n* **Competitive Benefits:** We offer a comprehensive benefits package, including health insurance, retirement plans, and generous paid time off.\n* **Inclusive Environment:** We are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected.\n\n**Current Openings:**\n* Senior Software Engineer (Ref: SSE001) - Requirements: 5+ years experience, proficiency in Java and Python.\n* Marketing Manager (Ref: MM002) - Requirements: Bachelor\'s degree in Marketing, 3+ years experience in digital marketing.\n* UX/UI Designer (Ref: UID003) - Requirements: Strong portfolio, expertise in design tools (e.g., Figma, Sketch).\n\nTo apply, please visit our online portal and submit your resume and a cover letter referencing the job ID. We look forward to hearing from you!\n','READING','Part 7 - Passage 040 (Web Page - Careers)',NULL),(204,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Important Update Regarding Your Order #789123\n\nDear Valued Customer,\n\nWe are writing to ------- (53) ------- you about an unforeseen delay in the shipment of your recent order, #789123, which included the \"Executive Leather Briefcase.\" Due to unexpected disruptions at our main distribution center, your package is now scheduled to be dispatched on June 5th, instead of the original date of June 2nd.\n\nWe sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. ------- (54) -------. We are working diligently to process all pending orders as quickly as possible. You will receive a new shipping confirmation email with tracking information once your order