y to find summer reading for the whole family.\n\nFurthermore, on the first day of the sale (Saturday, July 5th), we will be hosting a local author signing event from 2 PM to 4 PM. Don\'t miss the chance to meet your favorite local writers! We expect a large ------- (63) -------, so come early.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you at Readers\' Haven for our biggest sale of the year. Happy reading! Our store hours are Monday - Saturday, 10 AM - 7 PM, and Sunday 12 PM - 5 PM. These hours will remain the ------- (64) ------- during the sale week.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 016 (Advertisement - Bookstore Sale)',NULL),(207,NULL,NULL,6,'Effective time management is a crucial skill for success in both personal and professional life. Learning to manage your time well can reduce stress, increase productivity, and help you achieve your goals. One of the first steps is to ------- (65) ------- your tasks.\n\nCreate a to-do list and categorize items by urgency and importance. This helps you focus on what truly needs to be done first. ------- (66) -------. Another useful technique is to break down large projects into smaller, more manageable steps. This makes daunting tasks feel less ------- (67) ------- and easier to start.\n\nFinally, remember to schedule regular breaks. Working continuously without rest can lead to burnout and decreased efficiency. Taking short breaks can actually improve focus and ------- (68) ------- your overall performance.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 017 (Article Snippet - Time Management)',NULL),(208,NULL,NULL,6,'To: All Employees\nFrom: Cafeteria Management\nSubject: Exciting Changes at the Company Cafeteria!\n\nWe are pleased to announce some exciting updates to our company cafeteria, effective next Monday, July 21st. We have listened to your feedback and are making changes to ------- (69) ------- your dining experience.\n\nFirstly, we will be introducing a wider variety of healthy meal options, including more vegetarian and vegan choices. Our daily specials will also feature international cuisines. ------- (70) -------. Secondly, to better accommodate different work schedules, our operating hours will be extended. The cafeteria will now be open from 7:00 AM for breakfast until 6:00 PM for early dinner options.\n\nWe are also installing new self-service kiosks for faster ordering and payment. We believe these ------- (71) ------- will make your meal times more enjoyable and convenient. We welcome any further suggestions you may have. There is a suggestion box located near the entrance. Thank you for your continued ------- (72) -------.\n','READING','Part 6 - Passage 018 (Notice - Cafeteria Changes)',NULL),(209,NULL,NULL,6,'Subject: Your Recent Experience with TechSupport Pro\n\nDear Valued Customer,\n\nThank you for recently contacting TechSupport Pro. We hope that your technical issue was resolved to your ------- (73) -------.\n\nAt TechSupport Pro, we are constantly striving to improve our services. To help us achieve this, we would be grateful if you could take a few moments to complete a short survey about your recent support experience. ------- (74) -------. Your honest feedback is invaluable and will help us identify areas where we are doing well and where we can make ------- (75) -------.\n\nThe survey should take no more than 5 minutes to complete and can be accessed via the following link: [Survey Link]. All responses are confidential.\n\nThank you for your time and for helping us serve you better. We appreciate your ------- (76) -------.\n\nSincerely,\nThe TechSupport Pro Team','READING','Part 6 - Passage 019 (Email - Requesting Service Feedback)',NULL),(210,NULL,NULL,6,'To: All Warehouse Staff\nFrom: Jim Reynolds, Safety Officer\nDate: July 25, 2025\nSubject: Important Reminder: Warehouse Safety Procedures\n\nThis memo is a critical reminder to all warehouse personnel regarding the strict ------- (77) ------- to safety procedures. Maintaining a safe working environment is our top priority and requir